User guide for Data integration Tool (DIT)

Types of input files:
cat    type      format  varname   description
'in'   'varmap'  'ascii' 'na'      variable input to output mapping file
'in'   'inpath'  'na'    'na'      path to input data files
'out'  'outpath' 'na'    'na'      path to output data files
'in'   'metadat' 'ascii' 'na'      path to input metadata file

Types of data files
type    in       out        in      out     map      meta      ncol  nhead   Description
'data'  'infile' 'outfile'  inpath  outpath mappath  metapath  ncol  nhead   specs for regular data file
'meta'  'infile' 'outfile'  inpath  outpath mappath  unused    ncol  nhead   specs for metadata file


manipulation options
doit  type         file ind1  ind2   ind3  val1  val2  val3  txt1  txt2  txt3  Description
t     'mult_con'   num  var   0      0     con   0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  multiply variable var by con
t     'div_con'    num  var   0      0     con   0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  divide variable var by con
t     'add_con'    num  var   0      0     con   0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  add con to variable var
t     'sub_con'    num  var   0      0     con   0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  subtract con from variable var
t     'stats_var'  num  var   0      0     0.    0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  calculates statistics for variable
                                                                               var = variable number
									       calculates min, max, std, mean,number valid points
t     'rm_punct'   num  var   0      0     0.    0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  removes punctuation
                                                                               removes periods, replaces comma with semicolon
t     'replace_eq' num  var   0      0     val1  val2  0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  replace values = val1 with val2
                                                                               num= 1 (input data array) or 2 (output data array)
									       var=variable number as specified in varmap
t     'count_val'  num  var   0      0     miss  0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  counts the number of different values of a single variable
                                                                               use to count number of boreholes, number depths, etc.
                                                                               assumes the data is stacked in order in a single file
                                                                               num= 1 (input data array) or 2 (output data array)
									       var=variable number as specified in varmap
									       miss=missing value
t     'count_rec'  num  var   0      0     miss  0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  count valid records for variable
                                                                               num= 1 (input data array) or 2 (output data array)
									       var=variable number as specified in varmap
									       miss=missing value
t     'print_max'  num  var   0      0     miss  0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  print max and min values for one variable
                                                                               num= 1 (input data array) or 2 (output data array)
									       var=variable number as specified in varmap
									       miss=missing value
t     'print_mean' num  var   0      0     miss  0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  print mean and standard dev for one variable
                                                                               num= 1 (input data array) or 2 (output data array)
									       var=variable number as specified in varmap
									       miss=missing value
t     'rem_nodata' num  0     0      0     miss  0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  remove layers with no data
                                                                               num=1 (done to input data only)
									       miss=missing value
t     'rem_dup'    num  yr    mon    0     miss  0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  removes duplicate records assuming monthly data
                                                                               num=1 (done to input data only)
									       yr=variable number of year as specified in varmap
									       mon=variable number of month as specified in varmap
									       miss=missing value
t     'sort_inc'   num  var1  var2   0     0.    0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  sorts data in increasing order by var1 first and var2 second
                                                                               num=1 input data =2 output data
									       var1= first variable number in varmap (typically year)
									       var2= second variable number in varmap (typically month)
                                                                               assumes var1 and var2 have no missing values
t     'mid_mon'    date var   year   mon   0.    0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'  calculates midmonth date as a character string in the form YYYY-MM-DD
                                                                               num=2 only works for output data
									       date= output variable number for date
									       year= year variable number in varmap
									       mon= month variable number in varmap
t     'map_lookup' num  map   code   var   0.    0.    0.  'grid' 'lon' 'lat'  extracts variable from a map
                                                                               num=2 (done to output data only)
									       map=path number of map
									       code=path num ascii file mapping code num from map to text value
									       grid=grid name
									       lon=longitude variable name
									       lat=latitude variable name
t     'timezone'   num  map   in     out   0.   0.    0.    'na'  'na'  'na'   calculates time zone for point based only on longitude
                                                                               map=2 (outfile only)
									       in=input variable number (longitude)
									       out=output variably number (timezone) 
									       

var<=0 makes calculation for all variables
num=1  apply to input data file
num=2  apply to output data file
